%% Data Science Pipelines Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Dashboard
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy<br/>8443/TCP TLS
    participant API as DS Pipeline API Server<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant DB as MariaDB<br/>3306/TCP
    participant S3 as S3 Object Storage<br/>9000/TCP
    participant Tekton as Tekton Pipelines<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PA as Persistence Agent
    participant K8s as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Envoy as MLMD Envoy<br/>9090/TCP gRPC
    participant MLMD as MLMD gRPC Server<br/>8080/TCP gRPC
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard

    Note over User,Tekton: Flow 1: Pipeline Execution (User Submits Pipeline Run)
    User->>Router: POST /apis/v1beta1/runs<br/>HTTPS TLS, OAuth token
    Router->>OAuth: Reencrypt TLS<br/>8443/TCP
    OAuth->>OAuth: Validate OAuth token<br/>SAR check on Route
    OAuth->>API: Forward request<br/>HTTP 8888/TCP (localhost)
    API->>DB: Store pipeline metadata<br/>MySQL 3306/TCP, Password auth
    API->>S3: Store pipeline artifacts<br/>HTTP/HTTPS 9000/TCP, AccessKey/SecretKey
    API->>Tekton: Create PipelineRun CR<br/>HTTPS 443/TCP, ServiceAccount token
    Tekton-->>API: PipelineRun created
    API-->>OAuth: Pipeline run response
    OAuth-->>Router: HTTPS response
    Router-->>User: JSON response

    Note over PA,K8s: Flow 2: Pipeline Run Status Tracking
    PA->>K8s: Watch PipelineRun status<br/>HTTPS 443/TCP, ServiceAccount
    K8s-->>PA: PipelineRun status update
    PA->>API: Report run status<br/>HTTP 8888/TCP

    Note over Dashboard,MLMD: Flow 4: Dashboard Metadata Access
    Dashboard->>Envoy: Query metadata<br/>gRPC 9090/TCP (NetworkPolicy)
    Envoy->>MLMD: Forward gRPC<br/>8080/TCP
    MLMD->>DB: Query metadata<br/>MySQL 3306/TCP, Password
    DB-->>MLMD: Metadata results
    MLMD-->>Envoy: gRPC response
    Envoy-->>Dashboard: Metadata results

    Note over API,S3: Flow 3: Operator Health Checks (Reconcile)
    participant CTRL as Controller Manager
    CTRL->>DB: Health check<br/>MySQL 3306/TCP
    DB-->>CTRL: Connection OK
    CTRL->>S3: Health check<br/>S3 API 9000/TCP
    S3-->>CTRL: Connection OK
    CTRL->>K8s: Reconcile resources<br/>HTTPS 443/TCP
